<dl id="n12108n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12108n">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12108n"> 108(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> lustration </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Purification by washing. Cf. <cite>The Legend of Saint Ronan</cite>: All these circumambulations are performed in the direction of the sun: the relics of the saint leaving the church turn to the right and follow the sun, like in all ancient lustration rites, biblical, Roman, pradakshina, Hindu, Old Irish. </mm> </dd></dl>
